sed","1285–Male":"1285–Deceased","1310–Male":"1310–Deceased","1288–Female":"1288–Deceased","1288":"1288","1310":"1310","1285":"1285","1308":"1308","France":"France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Worsley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire): habitational name from Worsley in Lancashire or Worsley Farm in Rock (Worcestershire). The Lancashire placename may derive from an Old English personal name <i>Weorcgȳth</i> (genitive <i>Weorcgȳthes</i>) + Old English <i>lēah</i> ‘wood, woodland clearing’. The Worcestershire placename may take its name from a lost stream-name <i>Worf</i> + Old English <i>lēah</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Worsley was born in 1288, in France. She married Adam Whetehill in 1308, in France. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1288–":"1288–Surnud","1285–Male":"1285–Surnud","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1288–Female":"1288–Surnud","1288":"1288","1310":"1310","1285":"1285","1308":"1308","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1288–":"1288–Kuollut","1285–Male":"1285–Kuollut","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1288–Female":"1288–Kuollut","1288":"1288","1310":"1310","1285":"1285","1308":"1308","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"1288–":"1288–Décédée","1285–Male":"1285–Décédé","1310–Male":"1310–Décédé","1288–Female":"1288–Décédée","1288":"1288","1310":"1310","1285":"1285","1308":"1308","France":"France","lifeSummary":"Margaret Worsley est née en 1288, à France. Elle a épousé Adam Whetehill en 1308, à France. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"1288–":"1288–Verstorben","1285–Male":"1285–Verstorben","1310–Male":"1310–Verstorben","1288–Female":"1288–Verstorben","1288":"1288","1310":"1310","1285":"1285","1308":"1308","France":"Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Margaret Worsley wurde 1288 in Frankreich geboren. Sie hat 1308 in Frankreich Adam Whetehill geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1288–":"1288–Desede","1285–Male":"1285–Desede","1310–Male":"1310–Desede","1288–Female":"1288–Desede","1288":"1288","1310":"1310","1285":"1285","1308":"1308","France":"France"},"hu":{"1288–":"1288–elhunyt","1285–Male":"1285–elhunyt","1310–Male":"1310–elhunyt","1288–Female":"1288–elhunyt","1288":"1288","1310":"1310","1285":"1285","1308":"1308","France":"Franciaország"},"id":{"1288–":"1288–Telah Meninggal","1285–Male":"1285–Telah Meninggal","1310–Male":"1310–Telah Meninggal","1288–Female":"1288–Telah Meninggal","1288":"1288","1310":"1310","1285":"1285","1308":"1308","France":"Prancis"},"it":{"1288–":"1288–Deceduta","1285–Male":"1285–Deceduto","1310–Male":"1310–Deceduto","1288–Female":"1288–Deceduta","1288":"1288","1310":"1310","1285":"1285"